description: Johnny Carson, born in Iowa on this day in history, Oct. 23, 1925, went on to become the iconic and Emmy Award-winning host of "The Tonight Show." Here's his story.

title: Former State Department official reasons for resigning over ‘lethal assistance’ to Israel are 'unbelievable'
description: 'The Big Weekend Show' co-hosts discuss a former State Department official resigning over the Biden administration's response to the Israel-Hamas war.

title: Argentina election: Milei underperforms, but still reaches second round runoff against establishment's Massa
description: Argentines went to the polls tonight in the first round presidential election, amidst rising inflation and poverty. Congressman Javier Milei, and Economy Minister Sergio Massa will face off in the second round.

title: Rapper Blueface turns private suite at Rams game into personal strip club, then proposes to girlfriend
description: Blueface, a Los Angeles-based rapper, turned a private section of SoFi Stadium at Sunday's Rams game against the Steelers into his own personal strip club.

title: Hamas terrorists had instructions for using cyanide-based chemical bombs, linking to Al Qaeda: reports
description: Hamas terrorists who died while invading Israel on Oct. 7 were reportedly found to have USB devices with instructions on cyanide-based chemical bombs.

title: Broncos get late field goal, interception for victory over Packers
description: Will Lutz knocked down a 52-yard field goal and P.J. Locke came up with a late interception to give the Denver Broncos a win over the Packers.

title: Seahawks keep Cardinals blanked in second half en route to victory
description: Kenneth Walker III ran for 105 yards as the Seattle Seahawks defense held their division rival, the Arizona Cardinals, scoreless in the second half for the victory.

title: Steelers fight back from fourth-quarter deficit to beat Rams
description: The Pittsburgh Steelers outscored the Los Angeles Rams, 14-0, in the fourth quarter for a comeback victory on Sunday afternoon in Southern California.
